{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The state and the city should seize this moment to find more lasting ways to sustain and upgrade the system.", "abstract": "Editorial asks where $29.8 billion in capital spending needed by New York State's Metropolitan Transportation Authority over next five years will come from; asserts budget experts from both city and state must work together to create a reasonable plan for sharing costs of maintaining infrastructure of nation's largest mass transit system; argues further that challenge is not just solving current budgetary crisis but planning for healthy fiscal future of system that supports millions of residents in New York region. ", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "18", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [], "original": "By THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "organization": "THE EDITORIAL BOARD"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/05/opinion/who-will-fund-the-mta.html", "lead_paragraph": "The state and the city should seize this moment to find more lasting ways to sustain and upgrade the system.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Who Will Fund the M.T.A.?", "main": "Who Will Fund the M.T.A.?", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Editorial"}, "_id": "55c1b96438f0d8746697cf2f", "word_count": "429", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 366, "url": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "366"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2015/08/05/opinion/05wed3web/05wed3web-th